title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x\sqsubseteq  y:D]]></fr:tex> be two elements of a dcpo <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[D]]></fr:tex>; we say that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex> is <fr:em>strictly below</fr:em> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[y]]></fr:tex>, written <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x\sqsubset  y]]></fr:tex>, if whenever <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[y\sqsubseteq \bigsqcup _{1+\phi }{\mathopen {}\left  [x\mid  y\right  ]\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> we have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\phi =\top ]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p><fr:p>(Adapted from <fr:link
type="local"
href="dejong-2023-thesis.xml"
addr="dejong-2023-thesis"
title="Domain theory in constructive and predicative univalent foundations">Tom de Jong’s thesis</fr:link>.)</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter><fr:tree
